<h3>Hosted by the Open Networking Foundation</h3> 

<h4>Welcome to the 2021 P4 Workshop!</h4>
<p>
The 2021 P4 Workshop is an exciting and informative virtual event. It is intended to incorporate insights and perspectives from the P4 community from around the world, and will include focused segments on:
<br/>
<ul>
<li>P4 language</li>
<li>P4 targets</li>
<li>P4 use cases</li>
<li>SDN use cases</li>
<li>P4 target tutorials</li>
</ul>
<br/>
This event is an opportunity for the P4 ecosystem to share knowledge and experiences with the broader community and to facilitate collaboration. It will include live keynotes May 18, 19 and 20, as well as on-demand presentations and panel discussions. There is no fee for participants to join and all presentations will be made publicly available after the event.<br/>
<br/>
For full details like CFP information, registration, agenda, and technical program committee, please visit the master event page on <a href="https://opennetworking.org/events/2021-p4-workshop/">ONF's website</a>.<br/>
<br/>
We look forward to 'seeing' you there! 
<p/>
